description: Rabbit is higher in protein than other meats, lower in fat, and has less calories.
Rabbit meat also contains Potassium that helps with fluid regulation and helps remove salts from the body.
Rabbit meat has been recommended for special diets such as for heart disease patients, diets for the elderly, whose metabolism has slowed and digestion is compromised, due to illness or life stage.
